    <tr>
     <td align="RIGHT" width="20" valign="TOP"><img width="20" height="20" src="/devenglish/readingspace/images/cleardot.gif"></td>
     <td align="RIGHT" width="9" valign="TOP"><img width="9" height="10" src="/devenglish/readingspace/images/cleardot.gif"></td>
     <td bgcolor="#FFFFFF" align="RIGHT" width="99" valign="TOP" colspan="2">&nbsp;</td>
     <td bgcolor="#FFFFFF" align="LEFT" width="479" valign="TOP"> <br><p><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2">Click on a topic to learn more about how to use ReadingSpace, or just scroll down the web page to read the topics in order. </font></p> 
      <ul></ul><p></p><li><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2"><a href="#order"> Test Order</a> </font></li> <li> <font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2"> <a href="#How to Fill Out Quizzes">How to Fill Out Quizzes</a> </font></li> <li> <font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2"> <a href="#Sending Your Answers to Your Instructor">Sending Your Answers to Your Instructor</a><br></font></li><li><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2"> <font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2"> <a href="#Email to Instructor">Email to Instructor </a><br></font></font></li><li><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2"><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2"> <font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2"> <a href="#Print Your Quiz">Print Your Quiz </a><br></font></font></font></li><li><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2"><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2"><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2"> <font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2"> <a href="#Can I Save My Answers">Can I Save My Answers?</a> </font> </font></font></font></li><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2"><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2"> <li> <p><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2"> <a href="#Technical">Technical Support</a> </font> </p></li> </font></font><p></p> <br><br><p><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" color="#0063CE" size="3"><b><a name="order">Test Order</a></b></font></p><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2">Students should take the Pretests first. The Pretests assess your current skill level. A rejoinder follows each answer to examine whether you've answered correctly or need further practice. <br><br> After you have completed the Pretests, use the Practice Tests to enhance your reading skills. The practice tests allow you to identify and develop 10 essential skills. Take advantage of the helpful hints and suggestions that accompany each question to learn effective reading strategies. <br><br> Finally, the Mastery Tests allow you to determine if you understand how to apply the tips provided during the Practice Tests. As in the previous sections, you'll have the advantage of rejoinders that evaluate the accuracy of each answer.<br><br><p><a href="#Contents">Back to Table of Contents</a></p><p> </p><p><b><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" color="#0063CE" size="3"><a name="How to Fill Out Quizzes">How to Fill Out Quizzes</a></font></b> </p> <p>Each test in ReadingSpace begins with a short reading. Read the material carefully, then answer the series of questions that follow. </p> <p>To answer multiple choice and true/false questions, simply click on the answer you think is correct. You may change your mind as many times as you like. If you decide to change your answer, just click on the answer you think is correct. Your first selection will be cleared, and your new answer will be selected.</p> <p>To answer the essay questions, enter your essay in the text box beneath the essay question. To begin writing, place your mouse arrow over the text box and click once. A flashing cursor will now be inside the text box and you can begin typing. Type as if you were working on a word processor or a typewriter. Don't worry about the size of the text box and try to make your lines fit inside of itÂ—it will automatically scroll your writing down to the next line. If you need to go back and look at parts of your answer that are no longer visible in the text box, use the <i>scrollbar</i> on the right-hand side of the text box to move the text into view. The top arrow button scrolls the text up toward the beginning; the bottom arrow scrolls the text down toward the end. </p></font> <p><a href="#Contents">Back to Table of Contents</a> </p><p> </p> <p><b><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" color="#0063CE" size="3"><a name="Sending Your Answers to Your Instructor">Sending Your Answers to Your Instructor</a></font></b><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2"> </font></p><p><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2">Once you've finished one of the ReadingSpace tests, you need to send your answers to your instructor. At the bottom of each web page, you'll see a button labeled Submit Quiz. It looks like this: </font></p><p></p>
      <form>
       <font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2"><input name="B1" type="SUBMIT" value="Submit Quiz"> <p>Press this button when you are finished filling in your answers. You will be forwarded to a new web page that lists the questions and your answers to them. At the bottom of this page are two buttons: </p><p></p>
        <form>
         <a href="#Email to Instructor"><input name="B1" type="SUBMIT" value="Email to Instructor"></a> 
         <a href="#Print Your Quiz"><input name="B1" type="SUBMIT" value="Print Quiz"></a>
        </form><br> Press the appropriate button. <p></p></font>
      </form><b><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" color="#0063CE" size="2"><a name="Email to Instructor">Email to Instructor</a></font></b><p></p><p><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2">If you want to email your answers to your instructor, press the <b>Email to Instructor</b> button. You will be forwarded to a new web page where you will be asked for some information before you can email your quiz. </font></p><p><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" color="#0063CE" size="2"><i>Enter Information</i></font></p><p><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2">You will be asked to enter your name, your instructor's name, and the name of the class or course you are taking into text boxes. You will also be asked to enter your email address and your instructor's email address. </font></p><p><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2"><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" color="#0063CE" size="2"><i>What if I Don't Have an Email Address?</i></font></font></p><p><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2"><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2">If you don't have an email address of your own, don't worry. Notice the <i>option buttons</i> below the text boxes. They look like this:</font> </font></p><p></p>
      <form>
       <font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2"><input name="R1" type="RADIO" value="V1" checked>Send to both student and instructor. <input name="R1" type="RADIO" value="V1">Send only to instructor.<p><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2">If you don't have an email address of your own, simply select <b>Send only to instructor</b> by clicking on the option button next to it. Only your instructor will receive the completed quiz.</font></p><p><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" color="#0063CE" size="2"><i>HTML or Text?</i></font></p><p><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2">You'll also notice option buttons that allow you to choose between <b>Send as text</b> and <b>Send as HTML</b>. Unless your instructor has specifically asked you to send your quiz as HTML, leave this option <b>Send as text</b>.</font></p><p><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" color="#0063CE" size="2"><i>One Last Confirmation</i></font></p><p><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2">When you've entered all the appropriate information, press the <b>Confirm Email</b> button. You will be forwarded to a confirmation web page that provides a summary of both the email addresses and the quiz. Review the email addresses to make sure they are correct. Use the <b>Back</b> button to return to earlier web pages if you need to make changes.</font></p><p><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2">When you're ready to send the email, return to this confirmation web page and hit the <b>Send Email</b> button.</font></p><p><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" color="#0063CE" size="2"><i>How to Get Back Home</i></font></p><p><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2">You will be forwarded to one more summary web page that looks much like the last web page, except that it announces <b>Email Sent</b>. You'll also notice a hyperlink in the center of the web page: ReadingSpace Home. Click on this to return to the opening page of the ReadingSpace website.</font></p> <p><a href="#Contents">Back to Table of Contents</a></p><p> </p><p></p></font>
      </form> <p></p><p><b><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" color="#0063CE" size="2"><a name="Print Your Quiz">Print Your Quiz </a></font></b><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2"> </font></p><p><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2"><i><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" color="#0063CE" size="2">Enter Information </font></i></font></p><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" color="#0063CE" size="2"></font><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2"> <p>If you pressed the <b>Print Quiz</b> button, you will be forwarded to a new web page, where you will be asked to enter your name, your instructor's name, and the name of the class or course you are taking into <i>one-line text boxes</i>. </p><p>When you are done, press the <b>Go to Printable Page</b> button.</p></font><p></p><p><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" color="#0063CE" size="2"><i>The Printable Page</i></font><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2"> </font></p><p><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2">You will be forwarded to a web page that has your quiz and your answers formatted for easy printing. Click your browser's Print Button, located on the same toolbar as the <b> Back</b> and <b>Forward</b> buttons. </font></p><p><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2">Depending on what browser you use, the web page may start printing straight away, or a print dialog box may open. If the dialog box opens, select the printer you want to use and enter the number of copies you would like to print, then hit the <b>Print</b> button.</font></p><p></p> <p><a href="#Contents">Back to Table of Contents</a></p> <p><br><b><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" color="#0063CE" size="2"><a name="Can I Save My Answers">Can I Save My Answers?</a></font></b><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2"></font></p><p><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2">It's important to understand that you cannot save your answers to your hard drive or floppy disk. If you don't print or email your answers when you are done, and you happen to close your browser, you will lose your answers.</font></p><p><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2"><a href="#Contents">Back to Table of Contents</a></font></p><p><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2"> </font></p><p></p> <b><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" color="#0063CE" size="3"><a name="Technical">Technical Support</a></font></b><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2"> <p>Technical support is available at <a href=" http://college.hmco.com/how/how_techsupp.html">http://college.hmco.com/how/how_techsupp.html</a>. Clicking on the Tech Support link at the bottom of every ReadingSpace page will display technical support information.</p></font> <p></p><p><a href="#Contents">Back to Table of Contents</a></p> <br></td>
